definition.value: A short-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of butyric acid.
An acyl CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of caffeic acid.
A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of cholic acid.
A medium-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of lauric (dodecanoic) acid.
